1.title: Blind Auditions 1
1.plot: The first blind audition of the very first season in the UK. There are four coaches, who turn around in their chairs when they hear a performer they want in their team. If there are more coaches who want a performer, he or she gets to choose who they want as their coach.

2.title: Blind Auditions 2
2.plot: It was the second blind audition of the first season. Sir Tom Jones has now 6 performers in his team, Jessie J has 5, Danny O'Donoghue has 4 and Will.I.Am has 3 performers.

3.title: Blind Auditions 3
3.plot: It was the third blind audition of the first season. Sir Tom Jones, Jessie J and Danny O'Donoghue have now 8 performers in their team, while Will.I.Am has only 7.

4.title: Blind Auditions 4
4.plot: It was the last blind audition of the season and all the coaches now have their entire team put together, consisting of 10 performers.

5.title: Battles 1
5.plot: The battles from team Will.I.Am were: Jenny Jones vs. Joelle Moses - I'm every woman (Chaka Khan) and Tyler James vs. Heshima Thompson - Yeah 3x (Chris Brown) and Jay Norton vs. Jaz Ellington - I heard it through the grape vine (Marvin Gaye). The battles from team Danny O'Donoghue were: Max Milner vs. Bill Downs - Beggin' (Madcon) and Bo Bruce vs. Vince Freeman - With or without you (U2). The battles from team Sir Tom Jones were: Aundrea Nyle vs. Sam Buttery - A little less conversation (Elvis Presley ft. JXL) and Deniece Pearson vs. Ruth Brown - No one (Alicia Keys)....

6.title: Battles 2
6.plot: The battles from team Jessie J were: Cassius Henry vs. David Faulkner - Beat it (Michael Jackson) and Ruth-Ann St. Luce vs. Ben Kelly - I wanna dance with somebody (Whitney Houston) and Becky Hill vs. Indie and Pixie - Irreplaceable (Beyoncé). The battles from team Sir Tom Jones were: Barbara Bryceland vs. Leanne Mitchell - The edge of glory (Lady Gaga) and Lindsey Butler vs. Matt and Sueleen - Born to run (Bruce Springsteen) and Adam Isaac vs. Denise Morgan - Use somebody (Kings of Leon). 1.title: Blind Auditions 1
1.plot: In this packed episode auditionees include a Scottish fireman who melts the heart of new coach Rita, a well-known soap star's daughter who brings the audience to tears and a TV return for one of the nation's most well-loved children's characters. The coaches start the show with a blistering performance of Republica's '90s hit Ready to Go before they take to the chairs for the first of seven blind audition programmes.

2.title: Blind Auditions 2
2.plot: Superstar coaches will.i.am, Sir Tom Jones, Rita Ora and Ricky Wilson hear from Yorkshire lass Jade Hewitt who works in a crisp factory by day but channels her inner Beyoncé by night. We also meet Classical Reflection - identical 19-year-old mirror twins from Peterborough who finish each other sentences, study the same subjects and who even passed their driving tests on the same day. Plus Billy Bottle and Martine, a happily married hippy couple from Devon who create an unlikely bond with will.i.am.

3.title: Blind Auditions 3
3.plot: Much to Sir Tom's delight, this episode sees many Welsh faces behind the spinning chairs. Schoolteacher Joe Woolford, gym cleaner Stephanie Webber and Lady Gaga tribute act Liss Jones are amongst the ten hopefuls eager to gain a spot on one of the teams. We also hear from Esmee Denters - a YouTube sensation once signed with Justin Timberlake's record label - and school disco favourite Black Lace's Dene Michael returns to the stage.

4.title: Blind Auditions 4
4.plot: The blind auditions continue as superstar coaches will.i.am, Sir Tom Jones, Rita Ora and Ricky Wilson compete to ensure they secure the best voices on their teams. There are many surprises behind the red chairs including trumpet-playing Dawn 'with the horn' Allen, Welshman Cai Williams and Tim Arnold, aka the Soho Hobo. The judges also hear from Liverpool duo The Mac Bros.

5.title: Blind Auditions 5
5.plot: Tonight we hear from celebrity chauffeur booker Vikesh Champaneri, 19-year-old Essex rapper Brooklyn and former lead singer from 80s boyband Brother Beyond, Nathan Moore.

6.title: Blind Auditions 6
6.plot: The competition is now fiercer than ever as places on each team become increasingly limited. The judges hear from Beckenham duo the Rise, spoken-word poet Lara Lee and Damian Dalton Smith - older brother of actress Sheridan Smith.

7.title: Blind Auditions 7
7.plot: This is the last chance for artists to claim the remaining places on the coaches' teams. In this final round we hear from Warrington Disney princess Sarah Dunn, singing waiter Mitch Miller and Tina Turner impersonator Andrew Marc.

8.title: Battles 1
8.plot: As the battles commence, the premise is simple: one song - two voices - one winner. Each battle sees two artists from the same team compete against each other in a vocal showdown. After each battle, the artists' own coach must decide who will progress to the knockout stage - and who will be sent home. But it's not quite over for the losing artist. The other coaches can steal a losing artist for their own team. Each coach gets two steals - if they missed out on an act during the blind auditions, this is their chance to finally grab them.

9.title: Battles 2
9.plot: In a nail-biting final battle, the remaining artists of each team take to the stage to secure their places in the next round. Will they be able to convince the coaches that they have what it takes to be this year's winner of The Voice UK? Superstar coaches will.i.am, Sir Tom Jones, Rita Ora and Ricky Wilson will each take eight artists through to the Knockouts stage.

10.title: Knockout 1
10.plot: Emma Willis and Marvin Humes present the first of the knockout rounds. The coaches watch each of their eight contestants perform and must choose the best three acts from their team to continue on to the live shows. Rita and will.i.am pit their remaining artists against each other to compete in one last round before the live shows. It is now the artists who take control - they must each choose one 'killer song' that they think will give them the best chance to impress their coach. Which of Rita's acts, including Welsh school teacher Joe Woolford, Liss Jones or duo ...

11.title: Knockout 2
11.plot: It's now up to Ricky Wilson and Sir Tom Jones to pit their remaining artists against each other in one last contest before the live shows. Sir Tom Jones must choose between acts including bricklayer Sasha Simone, gospel-singing duo Joyful Soundz and spoken-word poet Lara Lee. Over on Ricky Wilson's team, will Scottish fireman Stevie McRorie, schoolgirl Claudia Rose, or powerhouse Hannah Symons have what it takes to make it through to the next round?

12.title: Live Quarter Final
12.plot: For the first time this series Rita Ora, will.i.am, Ricky Wilson and Sir Tom Jones bring their teams to perform live in front of the nation in a bid to secure their place in the semi-finals. In the first live show of the series, the viewers at home get their first chance to vote on who remains in the competition and who goes home. Plus live performances from Olly Murs and 2014's winner Jermain Jackman, performing his debut single How Will I Know.

13.title: Live Quarter Final Results
13.plot: Emma Willis and Marvin Humes reveal the results of the public vote and announce who has gained a coveted place in the semi-finals.

14.title: Live Semi-Final
14.plot: The semi-final sees the coaches' remaining eight acts perform live in front of the nation. Each act performs one solo song and one song with their coach and remaining team. They then face the public vote. The acts gaining the highest number of votes will go through to the final.

15.title: Live Final
15.plot: The contestants have made it through the blind auditions, battles and knockouts - now only four remain. In the grand final, the power lies with the viewers as the final four artists face the public vote in a bid to be crowned winner of The Voice UK 2015. Each artist performs one solo song, and Sir Tom Jones, Ricky Wilson, Rita Ora and will.i.am perform one song with their remaining artists. The viewers will also be treated to a special performance from Paloma Faith and the Script.
